[Feature: Build the leave management module — Phase 1: Shared types, base repository, and Fastify migration]

Update src/shared/types/index.ts: replace the existing simplified types with the canonical TypeScript types and enums. Define LeaveType (annual, sick, emergency), LeaveRequestStatus (DRAFT, SUBMITTED, APPROVED, REJECTED, CANCELLED), and interfaces: Employee (with employeeNumber, firstName, lastName, email, managerId, department, hireDate, terminationDate, employmentStatus, createdAt, updatedAt, deletedAt), LeaveRequest (with id, employeeId, leaveTypeId, startDate, endDate, reason, status: LeaveRequestStatus, approvedBy, approvedAt, createdAt, updatedAt), LeaveBalance (with id, employeeId, policyId, totalEntitlement, usedDays, remainingDays, fiscalYear, status, createdAt, updatedAt), LeavePolicy, Notification, AuditRecord, ValidationResult. Also define all DTOs: CreateLeaveRequestDto, UpdateLeaveRequestDto, LeaveRequestQueryParams, CreateLeaveBalanceDto, CreateNotificationDto, CreateAuditRecordDto, CreateEmployeeDto, UpdateEmployeeDto, CreateLeavePolicyDto, UpdateLeavePolicyDto. Create src/shared/base-repository.ts with an abstract BaseRepository<T> class that enforces GP-001 (common CRUD contract wrapping the pg Pool). Replace Express with Fastify in src/app.ts (create Fastify instance, register plugins) and src/index.ts (use Fastify listen). Add fastify dependency to package.json. This phase has zero module dependencies and establishes the foundation every subsequent phase imports from.

Phase architecture notes:
Establishes the canonical type system and Fastify runtime. All subsequent phases import types from src/shared/types/index.ts and extend BaseRepository from src/shared/base-repository.ts. The existing src/shared/db/connection.ts Pool export is consumed by BaseRepository.

